  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Strategy:<br />
This deck is pretty straight forward, even if it is literally the size of a brick when it&#39;s in card sleeves. You want to move your Fellowship twice per turn, but stop at the sanctuaries to make sure you heal up. Most of the Free Peoples&#39; events can be used to either beef up your character&#39;s strength, or keep minions off your back (Pursuit Just Behind, Gondor&#39;s Vengeance, and Eregion&#39;s Trails all work great at offing minions). Of course you&#39;ll want to win the starting bid (I haven&#39;t had to go higher than 4 yet) to get The Prancing Pony out. If you don&#39;t no worries, that&#39;s what the Hobbit Farmers are for. Get Aragorn out and start moving. Here&#39;s a couple of card explainations:<br />
<br />
*Athelas: gets rid of those nasty Blade Tips. It&#39;s fun playing with them, but playing against them isn&#39;t exactly fun.<br />
*Double Shot: your bows out and fire away. After a couple archery wounds and perhaps some skirmishing, you can finish off any remaining minions with Pursuit Just Behind, then move to the next site. <br />
*Boromir, Son of Denethor: he&#39;s here because I can&#39;t seem to get my hands on more than one rare Boromir. Bah!<br />
*Cave Troll: well, he&#39;s not a Ringwraith, but he&#39;s @#$%in&#39; when you drop him after site 4. Might as well play with that bad mofo.<br />
*Black Breath: If you can&#39;t tell how nasty this is with Blade Tip, you should read those cards again. The only set back is the opponent&#39;s Athelas (if he/she happens to be playing them).<br />
<br />
That aboot sums it up, folks. Like I said, pretty straight forward. Kindly leave only CONSTRUCTIVE CRITICISM in your reviews. I&#39;ve only been playing for a week you know :) </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
